= How-to: Open a Port in {{gateway_product_name}} Firewall =

== Open an Incoming Port on {{gateway_product_name}} from the Outside ==

{{Firewall Custom}}

'''<code>Host</code> &rarr; <code>{{gateway_product_name}}</code>

'''<code>Internet</code> &rarr; <code>Host</code> &rarr; <code>{{gateway_product_name}}</code>

This will allow an incoming connection on {{Gateway product name}} originating from:

* if using VM: the host.
* if using physical isolation: the Internet.

{{Box|text=

'''1.''' {{Firewall Settings}}

'''2.''' Add. 

Replace <code>80</code> with the actual port you would like to open.

{{CodeSelect|code=
EXTERNAL_OPEN_PORTS+=" 80 "
}}

'''3.''' Save.

'''4.''' {{Reload_Firewall}}

The procedure is complete.
}}

== Open an Incoming Port on {{gateway_product_name}} for Connections Originating from {{Workstation product name}} ==

{{Firewall Custom}}

'''<code>{{Workstation product name}}</code> &rarr; <code>{{gateway product name}}</code>'''

This will allow incoming connections from {{Workstation product name}} to {{gateway product name}}.

It might be useful for [[Tor#Additional_SocksPorts|Tor additional <code>SocksPort</code>s]]. ('''<code>{{Workstation product name}}</code> &rarr; <code>{{gateway product name}}</code> &rarr; Tor <code>SocksPort</code>''')

{{Box|text=

'''1.''' {{Firewall Settings}}

'''2.''' Add.

Note: 
* Replace <code>9230</code> with the actual port you would like to open. 
* Replace <code>SOCKS_PORT_CUSTOM</code> with <code>SOCKS_PORT_ANOTHER</code> when using multiple connections. 
* Replace word <code>ANOTHER</code> with another unique word.

Up to {{project name}} version <code>15.0.1.7.2</code>.

{{CodeSelect|code=
SOCKS_PORT_CUSTOM=" 9230 "
}}

The syntax will change in later {{project name}} versions. <ref>
https://forums.whonix.org/t/internal-open-ports-setting/11404/1
</ref>

{{CodeSelect|code=
INTERNAL_OPEN_PORTS+=" 9230 "
}}

Adding both settings to the firewall settings file is okay.

'''3.''' Save.

'''4.''' {{Reload_Firewall}}

The procedure is complete.
}}

